  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "dauF4eBmngu3"
   },
   "source": [
    "## 3. ***Data Wrangling***"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "bKJF3rekwFvQ"
   },
   "source": [
    "### Data Wrangling Code"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "wk-9a2fpoLcV"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Remove invalid age entries\n",
    "df = df[(df['age'] >= 18) & (df['age'] <= 100)]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Clean column names\n",
    "df.columns = df.columns.str.strip().str.lower()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Strip whitespace and lowercase text data\n",
    "df = df.apply(lambda x: x.str.strip().str.lower() if x.dtype == 'object' else x)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Standardize gender categories\n",
    "df['gender'] = df['gender'].replace({\n",
    "    'f': 'female', 'female ': 'female', 'cis female': 'female', 'woman': 'female',\n",
    "    'm': 'male', 'male ': 'male', 'cis male': 'male', 'man': 'male',\n",
    "    'trans-female': 'transgender', 'trans male': 'transgender',\n",
    "    'non-binary': 'nonbinary', 'genderqueer': 'nonbinary', 'agender': 'nonbinary'\n",
    "})\n",
    "df['gender'] = df['gender'].apply(lambda x: x if x in ['male', 'female', 'transgender', 'nonbinary'] else 'other')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Drop duplicate entries\n",
    "df = df.drop_duplicates()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Drop rows with missing age, gender, or treatment\n",
    "df = df.dropna(subset=['age', 'gender', 'treatment'])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Final shape of cleaned data\n",
    "print(\"Cleaned dataset shape:\", df.shape)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "MSa1f5Uengrz"
   },
   "source": [
    "### What all manipulations have you done and insights you found?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "LbyXE7I1olp8"
   },
   "source": [
    "1. Removed Wrong Ages\n",
    "Deleted entries where age was too low (under 18) or too high (over 100).\n",
    "2. Cleaned Column Names\n",
    "Fixed messy column names by making them lowercase and removing extra spaces.\n",
    "3. Cleaned Text Data\n",
    "Removed extra spaces and made all text lowercase (like \" Yes \" → \"yes\").\n",
    "4. Fixed Gender Column\n",
    "Grouped all similar gender responses into 4 clear groups: male, female, transgender, nonbinary\n",
    "Everything else was labeled as other.\n",
    "5. Removed Duplicate Rows\n",
    "Got rid of any repeated survey responses.\n",
    "6. Handled Missing Values\n",
    "Removed rows where important values (like age, gender, or treatment) were missing.\n",
    "\n",
    "Insights:\n",
    "1. The dataset has 1259 survey responses, each one is about mental health in tech jobs.\n",
    "2. The questions include: Age, gender, country\n",
    "-Whether the person has had treatment for mental health\n",
    "-If their company supports mental health\n",
    "3. Some columns had missing values, especially questions like U.S. state and work interference.\n",
    "4. The gender column had many different ways of saying the same thing (like \"cis male\", \"M\", \"male \"), so I grouped them properly.\n",
    "5. The dataset is now clean, simple, and ready to start analyzing things like: How many people sought treatment\n",
    "-If mental health affects work\n",
    "-Differences between male and female respondents\n"
   ]
  },
